signatureAbility.signatureDescription: RAC receivers fight for every possible yard after making a catch. When they enter the zone, this ability increases their success rate on RAC catches against single coverage.
Receivers with this ability run sharper routes and catch more consistently while running in and out routes.
Some players thrive on making defenders look silly. When they enter the zone, this ability increases their fakeout rate on the next juke, spin or hurdle.
Ballcarriers with this ability have faster juke animations.
Ballcarriers with this ability can quickly shift momentum, change direction, and turn the corner without sacrificing speed.
Run Stuffers can singlehandedly disrupt an offense. When they enter the zone, this ability increases their win rate and block shed speed against one-on-one run blocks.
Defenders with this ability use faster run shed moves for a better chance at shedding blocks against inside zone plays.
Defenders with this ability can reach out of engaged blocks to tackle or sack nearby ballcarriers.
Defenders with this ability use faster run shed moves for a better chance at shedding blocks against outside zone plays.
Players with this ability have an increased chance to catch passes that have been tipped into the air.
Passers with this ability have perfect accuracy on all unpressured throws while their feet are set in the pocket (except on high/low throws).
Defenders with this ability have an increased success rate when using conservative or diving tackles.
